@alchemist 
When a product RETAILs for $5.00 that is the price a consumer pays. More casually we say it “goes for” $5.00.

I think the word is used often in comparison to what the item sells for wholesale. But I don’t often hear anyone say it “wholesales” for, say $3.50.

@PR Betz as the youth would say “OK boomer”. You don’t enjoy this type of puzzle and that’s fine. That doesn’t make it “stupid” or imply a “lack of regard for common sense”.  I’m sure there are venues that cater to the type of puzzle you prefer. Maybe seek those out.  Many enjoy the extra level of puzzling found particularly in the Thursday and Sunday puzzles - they have been this way for many years. If that’s not you, maybe try something different on those days.

I understand aversion to change, I hate when things I have got used to change, but when it happens, I either roll with it, get over it, or switch to something else. Sure I might gripe about it, but I realize it’s just personal preference. 😊


